&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Associate Director Newcastle System Band 8d&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are delighted to be able to offer an opportunity to join a team of senior partners in Collaborative Newcastle in order to continue to develop our system wide response to deliver the best health and care services and outcomes for people living in Newcastle.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Collaboration between local authority, primary care networks, voluntary organisations and our hospital and community service providers is well established and delivering some great results. However, we have lots more to accomplish and in order to make further progress we are looking to increase our resources through the appointment of an Associate Director to work in the Newcastle System. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is an exciting role which will offer you the chance to be part of a creative and vibrant team who believe through partnership that we can overcome the challenges faced across our local health and care systems and really make a difference to our patients and public.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For more information please speak to Jackie Cairns Director for the Newcastle System &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;jackiecairns@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;07944179679&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interviews will be held Thursday 19&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; November 2020 on Microsoft Teams&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We anticipate a high level of interest in this post therefore we would suggest you apply as soon as possible as the closing date may be brought forward&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
